      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUZZ SAW (3) returned from a seven-month spell and led all the way to easily account for his rivals over this course and distance last start. Might be ready to realise his potential this prep so is worth following. ZOUKING (2) has led for the judge in his two runs this prep, both over 1000m, but capitulated on each occasion. Fitter now and should give backers a sight. MISS DE BLAAS (7) had a seven-week let-up prior to a desperately close second over this distance at Coffs Harbour recently. Doesn't win out of turn but that latest effort was encouraging. SAPPHIRE KISS (1) made late ground to get up for third at her latest appearance over today's journey at Scone. Always seems to find one or two better - good exotics option. CUPID'S KISS (4) turned in an eye-catcher in a BM66 over this course and distance nine days ago. Veteran mare who cannot be ruled out.",
